If you did NOT execute this recovery, the host is compromised at the
shell level. The application's auth surface is no longer the bound on
what an attacker can do.

What to do:
  1. Pull SSH access logs for the production VPS around this timestamp.
  2. Rotate every secret in .env (SECRET_KEY, EMAIL_PEPPER, DB / Redis).
  3. Audit the host for unfamiliar SSH keys, sudoers entries, cron jobs.
  4. If the host can't be trusted, redeploy onto a fresh VM and rotate
     everything from .env.example.
